# Solaris-III Lore: History and Timeline

<!-- Sources: https://wutheringwaves.fandom.com/wiki/Timeline, https://wutheringwaves.fandom.com/wiki/Solaris-3 -->

## Solaris-III: Etymology and Cosmological Context

- **Name:** Solaris-III (also: Sol-III, Solaris)
- **Position:** Third planet from the star named **Sol** (also known in the Roya Frostlands as **Baldur**)
- The naming convention follows classic science-fiction tradition: star name plus distance number, unlike real exoplanets which use lowercase letters by order of discovery.
- The word _Solaris_ derives from the Latin _sōlāris_, meaning "solar" or "of the sun."
- The name is likely a thematic reference to Stanisław Lem's 1961 novel _Solaris_, which similarly features a world whose nature defies full human understanding.
- Before the Lament, Solaris possessed active spaceflight programs and had begun reaching beyond its own atmosphere — a capability that was entirely eliminated when the Etheric Sea enclosed the planet.
- All space exploration has been suspended in the Post-Lament Anthropocene. Despite this, the Court of Savantae managed to launch the **SkyArk Space Station** in the early Post-Lament era to study the Etheric Sea before it fully formed.

## Solaris-III: History — The Pre-Lament Era

- In the time before the Laments, Solaris-III was a planet with a functioning ecosystem, developed civilizations, and even emerging spaceflight technology.
- Ancient advanced societies existed, including a mysterious precursor referred to as the **Homeland Civilization**, which created the **Sentinels** (also called **Oracle Engines**) and dispatched them across the cosmos via massive mechanical carriers called **Exostriders**.
- The Homeland Civilization's purpose in creating and sending Sentinels appears to have been the protection of emerging civilizations on various planets from the Threnodians — entities capable of destroying civilizations by feeding on human despair.
- The Roya Frostlands region was once a lush, forested land before the first recorded global Lament transformed it into an ice-covered pole. This cataclysmic shift is the earliest documented example of the planet's axis altering due to Lament activity.
- Humanity had begun developing proto-cities and even rudimentary aerospace technology before the cascade of disasters began, though all records from this era are fragmentary and much has been lost.

## Solaris-III: History — The First and Second Global Laments

- The **first recorded global Lament** was also the one responsible for the polar shift: the Roya Frostlands, once covered in lush forests, was transformed into an endless ice sheet and became Solaris's new pole. This is the earliest verifiable civilizational catastrophe in known history.
- The **second recorded Lament** struck the Roya Frostlands directly and had a pivotal cosmic consequence: it was during this second Lament that the **Exostrider** — a colossal mechanical being created by the Homeland Civilization — descended through a portal called the **Stridergate**, accompanied by **Threnodian Aleph-1**.
- When Aleph-1 unleashed the **Void Storm** as part of this second Lament, the Exostrider countered it by shedding its own components and transforming them into the **Exoswarm** — biomechanical flora and fauna that replaced the extinct native species of Lahai-Roi.
- The Roya Tribe, the indigenous people of the region, were displaced by these events and eventually guided to migrate underground, establishing the underground civilization that would become **Lahai-Roi**.
- Each global Lament appears to have accelerated the Waveworn Phenomenon and further entrenched the Etheric Sea's grip on Solaris's atmosphere.

## Solaris-III: History — The Five Global Laments

- Over the course of recorded history — spanning approximately **10,000 years** before the Rover's arrival — Solaris-III has endured exactly **five global Lament events**, in addition to more than **350,000 regional Lament events** of smaller scope.
- Each global Lament reshapes significant portions of Solaris's geography, ecology, and social order, causing mass extinctions of both human and non-human life.
- The Lament is not a single event but a **recurring cycle**, whose triggers and underlying causation remain one of the most hotly debated questions among Solaris's scholars, particularly at Huaxu Academy and Startorch Academy.
- The current era that follows the most recent Lament is designated the **Post-Lament Anthropocene** — humanity's classification for the age of rebuilding, adaptation, and resistance.
- The Black Shores has developed a **predictive system** for Lament activity using the **Tethys System** and a global network of **Resonance Beacons**, allowing it to monitor Sentinel-related activity and Lament threat levels in real time.
- The **Fractsidus** seeks to trigger a sixth global Lament — the so-called **True Lament** — believing it to be necessary for humanity's ultimate evolution, rather than an extinction event.

## Solaris-III: History — Founding of Rinascita

- During the era of Lament disasters, the civilization of one archipelago was so devastated by the Lament and associated Waveworn events that a group of displaced refugees, including the founders of the **Fisalia family**, boarded a mass of ships known as the **Ark**.
- The Ark set sail on a perilous journey to find new land. The Fisalia family, guided by an unknown voice and the light of the **Genesis Nexus** — a piece of technology left behind by the **Sentinel Imperator** — led the fleet safely to a lush archipelago.
- One of these islands would eventually become **Ragunna**, the heart of the Rinascitan confederation.
- The early settlers of Rinascita came from vastly different cultural, ideological, and theological backgrounds. Their internal divisions — particularly the conflict between worshippers of the sky divinity **Imperator** and the sea divinity **Leviathan** — led to wars that ultimately gave rise to the first **Dark Tide** event.
- The rulers of Rinascita would gather at **Fagaceae Peninsula** for secret councils and carved oracles into stone and trees. In the earliest mythology of the region, two divinities shared power: Imperator ruling the skies, and Leviathan ruling the seas.
- The First Dark Tide was stopped by **Napoli II**, the first Primus of the Order of the Deep, using a Lantern given to him by Imperator. This event established **The Order of the Deep** as the spiritual and governmental authority of Rinascita.

## Solaris-III: History — Modern Era and the Rover's Arrival

- In the approximately **20 years before the Rover's arrival** (referred to as **Landing Date, or LD**), Solaris-III was already under elevated strain from Lament-adjacent activity: Threnodian-related frequencies were being detected across multiple regions.
- Approximately **three years before LD**, the **Battle Beneath the Crescent** took place in Norfall Barrens (Jinzhou, Huanglong), in which the Midnight Rangers under **General Geshu Lin** fought the forces of **Threnodian Ovathrax** at enormous cost. Geshu Lin disappeared after delivering a decisive blow.
- The Marino family, protectors of the Order Orphanage in Rinascita, were killed in a Tacet Discord attack while travelling to the New Federation around 20 years before LD. Their assets were liquidated, and their child **Phoebe** was sent to the Order Orphanage.
- Around the same period (~20 years before LD), **Lorelei** was molded by the Sentinel and commanded to restrain clouds in the Nimbus Sanctum to prevent Remnant Energy from dissipating, where she has dwelled ever since.
- The Rover's arrival coincides with a surge in Threnodian-related activity worldwide. **Ovathrax**'s revival in Chapter I triggers measurable frequency fluctuations in other nations. The Rover, as an amnesiac Arbiter and former leader of the Black Shores, is uniquely positioned to confront these threats.
